answers.body_markdown:
It is not possible to create meta-annotations in the current spec.

Take a look at `@Id` annotation:
```lang-java
@Target({METHOD, FIELD})
@Retention(RUNTIME)

public @interface Id {}
```

`ANNOTATION_TYPE` is not listed as a possible target, which is why you receive &quot;This annotation is not applicable to target &#39;annotation class&#39;&quot; error.

There is an open issue [Allow type level annotations to be used as meta-annotations #43](https://github.com/jakartaee/persistence/issues/43) created in 2013, sadly it is still not implemented in 2023.

